# Chatters - Real-Time Chat App

Chatters is a full-stack real-time chat application built with the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) and Socket.io for instant messaging. Users can sign up, log in, search contacts, send text and images, view online status, and update profiles.[1]

## Features
- User authentication (signup/login)
- Real-time messaging with Socket.io
- User search functionality
- Online/offline status indicators
- Image sharing in chats
- Unread message counters
- Profile editing with avatar upload
- Responsive three-column layout (sidebar, chat, profile)[1]

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, React Router, Axios, Socket.io-client, React Hot Toast
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Mongoose, Socket.io, bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken
- **Database**: MongoDB (Atlas)
- **Other**: Cloudinary (images), Google Fonts (Outfit)[1]

## Prerequisites
- Node.js v18+
- MongoDB Atlas account
- Cloudinary account[1]

## Quick Setup

### Frontend
```
cd client
npm install
npm install react-hot-toast axios socket.io-client
npm run dev
```
Opens at http://localhost:5173[1]

### Backend
```
mkdir server && cd server
npm init -y
npm install express mongoose socket.io cors dotenv bcryptjs jsonwebtoken nodemon
# Setup MongoDB connection and routes in index.js
npm run dev  # or npm run server
```
Configure `.env` with MongoDB URI, JWT secret, Cloudinary keys.[1]

## Project Structure
- `client/`: React frontend
- `server/`: Node.js backend
GitHub: https://github.com/khushikumari0202/Chatters[1]

## Key Highlights
- Tailwind CSS with custom fonts and scrollbars
- Components: Sidebar (users/search), ChatContainer (messages), RightSidebar (profile/media)
- Socket.io for real-time: messages, status updates, unread badges[1]

## Future Enhancements
- Group chats
- Typing indicators
- Message reactions
- Voice messages
- Push notifications
- Extended file sharing
- Dark mode[1]

